---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="Learn about The Welder's Guide — your trusted source for expert welding and fabrication content for professionals and hobbyists.">
  <section class="py-16">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4">
      <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-8 items-center md:items-start mb-12">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0">
          <img
            src="/author.jpg"
            alt="Frank Ciervo"
            class="w-64 h-64 object-cover rounded-2xl shadow-lg"
          />
        </div>
        <div>
          <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-1 font-heading">Meet Frank Ciervo</h1>
          <p class="text-lg text-primary font-semibold mb-4">Certified Welder & Founder of The Welder's Guide</p>
          <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
            Frank Ciervo is a certified welder and the founder of The Welder's Guide. With over 22 years of experience in the welding trade, Frank has worked across a wide range of industries — from structural steel and pipe welding to automotive fabrication and artistic metalwork. He earned his AWS Certified Welder credential early in his career and went on to achieve multiple endorsements including SMAW, GMAW, and GTAW processes. After 15 years running his own welding and fabrication shop, Frank created The Welder's Guide to provide both aspiring and experienced welders with clear, practical instruction on techniques, equipment, safety, and career development. He is passionate about trade education and mentors young welders entering the field. Frank lives in Pennsylvania, where his home workshop is always humming with the sound of a grinder.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-6 font-heading">About The Welder's Guide</h2>
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-text">
        <p class="text-lg text-text-muted mb-6">
          Thousands of hours under the hood, a shop full of grinders, and a passion for getting the bead just right — that's what drives The Welder's Guide. This isn't a content mill recycling Wikipedia articles about welding. Every guide we publish comes from real bench time, real mistakes, and the kind of hard-won knowledge you only get from burning through rod after rod until your welds are X-ray quality.
        </p>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">Our Mission</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
          The welding trade is experiencing a serious skilled labor shortage, and too many beginners give up because the learning curve feels overwhelming. We're building the resource we wish we had starting out — clear, no-nonsense instruction that treats you like a future journeyman, not a click to monetize.
        </p>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">What We Cover</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mb-6">
          <li>MIG, TIG, stick, and flux-cored welding techniques</li>
          <li>Welding safety best practices and PPE recommendations</li>
          <li>Material selection and joint preparation guides</li>
          <li>Equipment reviews and buying advice</li>
          <li>Blueprint reading and fabrication planning</li>
          <li>Certification preparation and career development</li>
        </ul>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">For Professionals</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
          Push your skills further with advanced technique breakdowns, metallurgy fundamentals, and code welding preparation. Whether you're chasing your next certification or looking to move into pipe welding, we've got you covered.
        </p>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">For Hobbyists</h2>
        <p>
          Setting up your first welder shouldn't require an engineering degree. We walk you through machine settings, joint prep, and technique with photos and plain language — so you spend less time making slag and more time building things you're proud of.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
